name: Aruba - Balance Of Trade
description: The quarterly net financial position of Aruba in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Aruba - Consumer Price Index Cpi
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Aruba - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Aruba.

name: Aruba - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in Aruba.
source: Ministerio di Finansas, Comunicacion, Utilidad y Energia

name: Aruba - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Aruba and purchased by foreign entities.

name: Aruba - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Aruba as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.

name: Aruba - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of Aruba.

name: Aruba - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: Aruba - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Aruba, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.
source: Ministerio di Finansas, Comunicacion, Utilidad y Energia

name: Aruba - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Aruba.
source: Ministerio di Finansas, Comunicacion, Utilidad y Energia

name: United Arab Emirates - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in the United Arab Emirates. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Argentina. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.

name: Argentina - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Argentina.

name: Argentina - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Argentina as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.
source: Banco Central de la Repblica Argentina

name: Argentina - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of Argentina. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.

name: Argentina - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the Argentina.

name: Argentina - GDP Deflator
description: The relative difference between the real and nominal GDPs of Argentina.

name: Argentina - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in Argentina as a percentage of its GDP.
source: Ministry of the Economy, Government of Argentina

name: Argentina - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Argentina, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: Argentina - GDP Growth Rate
description: The growth rate of the GDP of Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of Argentina.

name: Argentina - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: Argentina - GDP per capita PPP
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: Argentina - Government Spending
description: The yearly expenditure of the federal government of Argentina.

name: Argentina - Permits for Floor Space
description: The volume of building permits granted in Argentina measured in units of area.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - up to 15 Days Interbank Rate
description: The monthly average of the fifteen-day interbank rate in Argentina. This is the interest rate charged by banks lending money to other banks for repayment within fifteen days.

name: Argentina - Import Prices
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in import prices. The index rises if imports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Industrial Production
description: The year-over-year percent change in the monthly industrial production of Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - 35-Day Lebac Rate
description: The daily average of the money market rate in Argentina.

name: Argentina - Leading Economic Index
description: This index is comprised of ten leading economic indicators and is intended to predict the overall direction of the economy.

name: Argentina - Money Supply M0
description: The value of physical currency circulating in the economy and the liquid assets held by the central bank.

name: Argentina - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: Argentina - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: Argentina - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: Argentina - Wages In Manufacturing Index
description: This quarterly index tracks the average yearly real wage in the manufacturing sector of Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Minimum Monthly Wage
description: The minimum wage in Argentina.
source: Ministerio de Economia y Production, Republica Argentina (MECON)

name: Argentina - Crude Oil Production
description: Argentina crude oil production in barrels.

name: Argentina - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Argentina, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: Argentina - Population
description: The number of residents of Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Argentina. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Remittances
description: The annual net value of remittances into Argentina. Remittances are monies sent into Argentina by workers in foreign countries.

name: Argentina - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Social Security Rate
description: The tax on labor income in Argentina used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Argentina - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in Argentina used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Argentina - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in Argentina used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Argentina - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Argentina.

name: Argentina - Terms of Trade
description: The quarterly ratio of export prices to import prices in Argentina.

name: Argentina - Tourist Arrivals
description: The number of tourists visiting Argentina from foreign countries.

name: Argentina - Unemployed Persons
description: The total members of the labor force of Argentina who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: Argentina - Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of the labor force of Argentina who are unemployed and actively seeking work.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Argentina - Average Monthly Wage for registered employees in the private sector
description: This index tracks the average yearly wage in Argentina.
source: Instituto Nacional de Estadstica y Censos (INDEC)

name: Armenia - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Armenia in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.
source: National Statistical Service of the Republic of Armenia

name: Armenia - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Armenia - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Armenia expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Armenia - Consumer Credit
description: The amount of money owed by residents of a country, including mortgages, bank loans, credit card and other debt.

name: Armenia - Core Consumer Prices
description: This index tracks prices of consumer goods excluding food, energy and other items with high price volatility.

name: Armenia - Capital Flows
description: The quarterly net capital flow into Armenia for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.
source: National Statistical Service of the Republic of Armenia

name: Armenia - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Armenia, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Armenia - Core Inflation Rate
description: The rate of change of the core Consumer Price Index of Armenia.

name: Armenia - Consumer Confidence
description: This quarterly index tracks consumers' opinions about their current economic well-being and outlook for the economy. It provides insight into consumers' short-term spending, saving, and borrowing plans.

name: Armenia - Construction Output
description: Total construction spending in Armenia each month.

name: Armenia - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.
source: National Statistical Service of the Republic of Armenia

name: Australia - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Australia. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

description: Harmonized Indices of Consumer Prices (HICP) are economic indicators that provide official measures of consumer inflation in the Eurozone. These indices track changes in prices to consumer goods and services that are commonly purchased by households. The compilation methodology index is harmonized across EU countries.

name: Austria - House Price Index
description: This quarterly index tracks residential house prices in Austria. The index increases as housing becomes more expensive and decreases when it becomes cheaper.

name: Austria - Three Month Interbank Rate
description: The monthly average of the three-month interbank rate in Austria. This is the interest rate charged by banks on loans to other banks for repayment within three months.

name: Austria - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: Austria - Industrial Production
description: The year-over-year percent change in the monthly industrial production of Austria.

name: Austria - Interest Rate
description: The daily average of the central bank policy rate in Austria. This is the interest rate the central bank charges on loans to commercial banks.

name: Austria - Job Vacancies
description: The total number of job vacancies in Austria.

name: Austria - Unit Labour Costs
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in the share of labor in total production costs in Austria. The index rises when the share of labor rises and falls when the share of labor falls.

name: Austria - Loans to Private Sector
description: The total value of bank loans to the private sector of Austria.

name: Austria - Long Term Unemployment Rate
description: The fraction of eligible workers who have been unemployed and looking for work for an extended period of time. Long-term is twelve months in Europe and twenty-seven weeks in the United States.

name: Austria - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: Austria - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: Austria - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: Austria - Minimum Wages in Manufacturing Index
description: This monthly index tracks the minimum wage in the manufacturing sector of Austria.

name: Austria - Stock Market (ATX)
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in Austria.

name: Austria - Manufacturing Production
description: The monthly per cent change in manufacturing output.

name: Austria - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Austria. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Austria - New Orders
description: The market value of new orders of manufactured goods in Austria by month.

name: Austria - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Austria, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: Austria - Population
description: The number of residents of Austria.

name: Austria - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Austria. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: Austria - Producer Prices Change
description: The monthly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of Austria.

name: Austria - Gross Household Saving Rate
description: The percentage of disposal income saved in Austria

name: Austria - Remittances
description: The quarterly net value of remittances into Austria. Remittances are monies sent into Austria by workers in foreign countries.

name: Austria - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in Austria.

name: Austria - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in Austria.

name: Austria - Social Security Rate
description: The tax on labor income in Austria used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Austria - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in Austria used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Austria - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in Austria used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Austria - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Austria.

description: Total annual wages earned by the labor force of Austria.

name: Azerbaijan - Balance of Trade
description: The quarterly net financial position of Azerbaijan in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.
source: Central Bank of the Republic of Azerbaijan

name: Azerbaijan - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.
source: Central Bank of the Republic of Azerbaijan

name: Azerbaijan - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Azerbaijan expressed as a percentage of its GDP.
source: Central Bank of the Republic of Azerbaijan

name: Azerbaijan - Capital Flows
description: The quarterly net capital flow into Azerbaijan for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.
source: Central Bank of the Republic of Azerbaijan

name: Azerbaijan - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Azerbaijan, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Azerbaijan - Consumer Price Index Cpi
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.
source: The State Statistical Committee of the Republic of Azerbaijan

description: The growth rate of the prices in Azerbaijan.

description: The monthly net financial position of Bangladesh in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Bangladesh - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Bangladesh - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Bangladesh expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Bangladesh - Consumer Credit
description: The amount of money owed by residents of a country, including mortgages, bank loans, credit card and other debt.

name: Bangladesh - Capital Account
description: The monthly net capital flow into Bangladesh for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.

name: Bangladesh - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Bangladesh, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Bangladesh - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Bangladesh - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Bangladesh.

name: Bangladesh - Consumer Spending

name: Belarus - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Belarus in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Belarus expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Belarus - Consumer Credit
description: The amount of money owed by residents of a country, including mortgages, bank loans, credit card and other debt.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Capital Flows
description: The quarterly net capital flow into Belarus for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Belarus.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Consumer Spending
description: Total quarterly personal expenditure on goods and services in Belarus, excluding interest payments, land purchases, transfers abroad, business expenditures, and purchases of second-hand goods.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in Belarus.
source: Ministry for Taxes and Levies of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Belarusian Rubble
description: National currency of Belarus

name: Belarus - Changes in Inventories
description: The quarterly change in inventory levels in Belarus.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Total Gross External Debt
description: The total amount of public and private debt in Belarus owned by foreign creditors.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Employed Persons
description: The total number of employed (including self-employed) persons in Belarus.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Belarus and purchased by foreign entities.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Belarus. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Foreign Exchange Reserves
description: The market value of the foreign currency reserves held by Belarus.
source: National Bank of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Belarus.

name: Belarus - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Belarus.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Belarus as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.

name: Belarus - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of Belarus. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.
source: National Bank of the Republic Of Belarus

name: Belarus - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the Belarus.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in Belarus as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Belarus - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Belarus, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.
source: National Statistical Committee of the Republic of Belarus

name: Belarus - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of Belarus.

description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

description: The growth rate of the total value of outstanding loans to the private sector in Brazil.

name: Brazil - Loans to Private Sector
description: The total value of bank loans to the private sector of Brazil.

name: Brazil - Money Supply M0
description: The value of physical currency circulating in the economy and the liquid assets held by the central bank.

name: Brazil - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: Brazil - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: Brazil - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: Brazil - Minimum Monthly Wages
description: The minimum wage in Brazil.
source: The Institute for Applied Economic Research (IPEA)

name: Brazil - Stock Market (BOVESPA)
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in Brazil.

name: Brazil - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Brazil. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Brazil - Net PayrollsÂ
description: The monthly net employment change in the non-agricultural economic sectors of Brazil.
source: Ministrio do Trabalho e Emprego, MTE

name: Brazil - Crude Oil Production
description: Brazil crude oil production in barrels.

name: Brazil - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Brazil, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.
source: Secretaria da Receita Federal do Brasil

name: Brazil - Population
description: The number of residents of Brazil.
source: Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics (IBGE)

name: Brazil - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Brazil. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: Brazil - Private Sector CreditÂ
description: The monthly change in outstanding private debt in Brazil.

name: Brazil - Remittances
description: The monthly net value of remittances into Brazil. Remittances are monies sent into Brazil by workers in foreign countries.

name: Brazil - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in Brazil.
source: Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e Estatstica (IBGE)

name: Brazil - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in Brazil.
source: Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e Estatstica (IBGE)

name: Brazil - Services PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the overall health of the services sector in Brazil. Private sector reports on key quantitative indicators are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the services sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration in the indicators from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Brazil - Social Security Rate
description: The tax on labor income in Brazil used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Brazil - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in Brazil used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Brazil - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in Brazil used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Brazil - Sales Tax Rate | VAT
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Brazil.
source: Secretaria da Receita Federal do Brasil

name: Brazil - Terms of Trade
description: The monthly ratio of export prices to import prices in Brazil.

name: Brazil - Tourist Arrivals
description: The number of tourists visiting Brazil from foreign countries.

name: Brazil - Unemployed Persons
description: The total members of the labor force of Brazil who are unemployed and actively seeking work.
source: Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e Estatstica (IBGE)

name: Brazil - Unemployment Rate

source: Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e Estatstica (IBGE)

name: Brazil - Real Average Monthly Income

name: Barbados - Balance Of Trade

description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Barbados, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Barbados - Consumer Price Index Cpi
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Switzerland - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Switzerland - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Switzerland. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Costa Rica - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Costa Rica in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Costa Rica - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Costa Rica - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Costa Rica expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Costa Rica - Capital Flows
description: The quarterly net capital flow into Costa Rica for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.

name: Costa Rica - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Costa Rica, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Costa Rica - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Spain - Services PMI

Private sector reports on key quantitative indicators are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the services sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration in the indicators from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Estonia - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Estonia in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

description: This monthly index tracks consumers' opinions about their current economic well-being and outlook for the economy. It provides insight into consumers' short-term spending, saving, and borrowing plans.

name: Estonia - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

description: The growth rate of the prices in Estonia.

name: Euro area - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in Euro area.

name: Euro area - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in Euro area.

name: Euro area - Services PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the overall health of the services sector in Euro area. Private sector reports on key quantitative indicators are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the services sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration in the indicators from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Euro area - Unemployed Persons
description: The total members of the labor force of Euro area who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: Euro area - Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of the labor force of Euro area who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: Euro area - Youth Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of unemployed persons ages 15-29 in Euro area who are actively seeking work.

name: Euro area - Average Monthly Wage Per Worker
description: Total quarterly wages earned by the labor force of Euro area.

name: Euro area - Euro Area Wage Growth
Euro area - Zew Economic Sentiment Index
description: This monthly index tracks economists' expectations for the European economy.

name: Finland - Business Confidence
description: This monthly index tracks the outlook of representative firms on the future business climate of Finland.

name: Finland - Bank Lending Rate
description: The monthly average of the bank lending rate. The bank lending rate is the interest rate charged by banks on loans to the private sector.

name: Finland - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Finland in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Finland - Bankruptcies
description: The quarterly number of corporate bankruptcies in Finland.

name: Finland - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Finland - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Finland expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Finland - Car Registrations
description: The number of new car registrations per month in Finland.

name: Finland - Consumer Credit
description: The amount of money owed by residents of a country, including mortgages, bank loans, credit card and other debt.

name: Finland - Capital Flows
description: The monthly net capital flow into Finland for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.

name: Finland - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Finland, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Finland - Consumer Confidence
description: This monthly index tracks consumers' opinions about their current economic well-being and outlook for the economy. It provides insight into consumers' short-term spending, saving, and borrowing plans.

name: Finland - Construction Output
description: Total construction spending in Finland each month.

name: Finland - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Finland - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Finland.

name: Finland - Inflation Rate MoM
description: The monthly percent change consumer prices of Finland.

name: Finland - Consumer Spending
description: Total quarterly personal expenditure on goods and services in Finland, excluding interest payments, land purchases, transfers abroad, business expenditures, and purchases of second-hand goods.

name: Finland - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in Finland.

name: Finland - Capacity Utilization
description: The quarterly national output of Finland as a percentage of its potential national output.

name: Finland - Changes in Inventories
description: The quarterly change in inventory levels in Finland.

name: Finland - External Debt
description: The total amount of public and private debt in Finland owned by foreign creditors.

name: Finland - Employed Persons
description: The total number of employed (including self-employed) persons in Finland.

name: Finland - Export Prices
description: This monthly index tracks changes in the average price of exports in Finland. The value of this index is the current price level expressed as a percentage of the price level from 2000. The index rises if exports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: Finland - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Finland and purchased by foreign entities.

name: Finland - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Finland. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.

name: Finland - Foreign Exchange Reserves
description: The market value of the foreign currency reserves held by Finland.

name: Finland - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Finland.

name: Finland - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Finland.

name: Finland - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Finland as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.

name: Finland - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of Finland. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.

name: Finland - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the Finland.

name: Finland - GDP Deflator
description: The relative difference between the real and nominal GDPs of Finland.

name: Finland - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in Finland as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Finland - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Finland, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: Finland - GDP Growth Rate
description: The growth rate of the GDP of Finland.

name: Finland - Gross National Income
description: The total income earned by residents of Finland at home and abroad.

name: Finland - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of Finland.

name: Finland - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: Finland - GDP per capita PPP
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: Finland - Government Spending to GDP
description: Government spending in Finland as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Finland - Government Spending
description: The yearly expenditure of the federal government of Finland.

name: Finland - Government Bond 10Y
description: The average of the yield on ten-year government bonds in Finland.

name: Finland - Harmonised Consumer Prices
description: Harmonized Indices of Consumer Prices (HICP) are economic indicators that provide official measures of consumer inflation in the Eurozone. These indices track changes in prices to consumer goods and services that are commonly purchased by households. The compilation methodology index is harmonized across EU countries.

name: Finland - Housing Index
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in residential house prices in Finland. It increases when housing becomes more expensive and decreases when housing becomes cheaper.

name: Finland - Three Month Interbank Rate
description: The daily average of the three-month interbank rate in Finland. This is the interest rate charged by banks on loans to other banks for repayment within three months.

name: Finland - Import Prices
description: This monthly index tracks changes in import prices. The index rises if imports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: Finland - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: Finland - Industrial Production
description: The year-over-year percent change in the monthly industrial production of Finland.

name: Finland - Interest Rate
description: The daily average of the central bank policy rate in Finland. This is the interest rate the central bank charges on loans to commercial banks.

name: Finland - Job Vacancies
description: The total number of job vacancies in Finland.
source: Ministry of Employment and the Economy, Finland

name: Finland - Labour Costs
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in the share of labor in total production costs in Finland. The index rises when the share of labor rises and falls when the share of labor falls.

name: Finland - GDP YoYÂ
description: This index is comprised of ten leading economic indicators and is intended to predict the overall direction of the economy.

name: Finland - Labor Force Participation Rate
description: The percentage of working-age persons in Finland who are employed or seeking employment

name: Finland - Loans to Private Sector
description: The total value of bank loans to the private sector of Finland.

name: Finland - Long Term Unemployment Rate
description: The fraction of eligible workers who have been unemployed and looking for work for an extended period of time. Long-term is twelve months in Europe and twenty-seven weeks in the United States.

name: Finland - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: Finland - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: Finland - Wages in Manufacturing Index
description: This quarterly index tracks the average yearly real wage in the manufacturing sector of Finland.

name: Finland - Manufacturing Production

name: Finland - New Orders

name: Finland - Producer Prices

name: United Kingdom - Prime Lending Rate
description: The average of the prime lending rate in the United Kingdom. The prime lending rate is the interest rate charged by banks on short-term loans to their most credit worthy customers.

name: United Kingdom - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of the United Kingdom in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: United Kingdom - Bankruptcies
description: The quarterly number of corporate bankruptcies in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: United Kingdom - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of the United Kingdom expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: United Kingdom - Car Registrations
description: The number of new car registrations per month in the United Kingdom.
source: The Soc. of Motor Mfrs. and Traders

name: United Kingdom - Central Bank Balance Sheet
description: The value of assets less liabilities held by the central bank of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Claimant Count Change
description: The number of newly unemployed persons in the United Kingdom. Positive values indicate growing unemployment; negative values indicate falling unemployment.

name: United Kingdom - Consumer Credit
description: The amount of money owed by residents of a country, including mortgages, bank loans, credit card and other debt.

name: United Kingdom - Core Consumer Prices
description: This index tracks prices of consumer goods excluding food, energy and other items with high price volatility.

name: United Kingdom - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of the United Kingdom, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: United Kingdom - Core Inflation Rate
description: The rate of change of the core Consumer Price Index of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Consumer Confidence
description: This monthly index tracks consumers' opinions about their current economic well-being and outlook for the economy. It provides insight into consumers' short-term spending, saving, and borrowing plans.

name: United Kingdom - Construction Output
description: Total construction spending in the United Kingdom each month.

name: United Kingdom - Construction New Orders
description: The year-over-year percentage change in quarterly construction orders in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Corporate Profits
description: The quarterly net profit of corporations in the United Kingdom. (millions)

name: United Kingdom - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: United Kingdom - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Inflation Rate MoM
description: The monthly percent change consumer prices of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Consumer Spending
description: Total quarterly personal expenditure on goods and services in the United Kingdom, excluding interest payments, land purchases, transfers abroad, business expenditures, and purchases of second-hand goods.

name: United Kingdom - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Capacity Utilization
description: The quarterly national output of the United Kingdom as a percentage of its potential national output.

name: United Kingdom - Changes in Inventories
description: The quarterly change in inventory levels in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Households Disposable Income
description: The household income remaining after taxes, deductions and interest payments, used for consumption and saving.

name: United Kingdom - Employment Change
description: The monthly change in the total number of employed persons in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Gross External Debt
description: The total amount of public and private debt in the United Kingdom owned by foreign creditors.

name: United Kingdom - Employed Persons
description: The total number of employed (including self-employed) persons in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Export Prices
description: This monthly index tracks changes in the average price of exports in the United Kingdom. The value of this index is the current price level expressed as a percentage of the price level from 2000. The index rises if exports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: United Kingdom - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by the United Kingdom and purchased by foreign entities.

name: United Kingdom - CBI Industrial Trends Orders
description: The change in the total value of new orders in the manufacturing sector of the United Kingdom, including raw materials and intermediate goods.

name: United Kingdom - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in the United Kingdom. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.

name: United Kingdom - Foreign Exchange Reserves
description: The market value of the foreign currency reserves held by the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Food Inflation
description: The growth rate of food prices in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of the United Kingdom as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.

name: United Kingdom - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of the United Kingdom. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.

name: United Kingdom - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - GDP Deflator
description: The relative difference between the real and nominal GDPs of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in the United Kingdom as a percentage of its GDP.

name: United Kingdom - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in the United Kingdom, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: United Kingdom - GDP Growth Rate
description: The growth rate of the GDP of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Gross National Income
description: The total income earned by residents of the United Kingdom at home and abroad.

name: United Kingdom - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: United Kingdom - GDP per capita PPP
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: United Kingdom - Government Spending to GDP
description: Government spending in the United Kingdom as a percentage of its GDP.

name: United Kingdom - Government Spending
description: The yearly expenditure of the federal government of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Government Bond 10Y
description: The average of the yield on ten-year government bonds in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Harmonised Consumer Prices
description: Harmonized Indices of Consumer Prices (HICP) are economic indicators that provide official measures of consumer inflation in the Eurozone. These indices track changes in prices to consumer goods and services that are commonly purchased by households. The compilation methodology index is harmonized across EU countries.

name: United Kingdom - House Price Index
description: This monthly index tracks changes in residential house prices in the United Kingdom. It increases when housing becomes more expensive and decreases when housing becomes cheaper.

name: United Kingdom - Housing Starts
description: The number of houses whose construction started the previous quarter in the United Kingdom.
source: Dept. For Communities & Local Gov., UK

name: United Kingdom - British Pound LIBOR Three Month Rate
description: The daily average of the three-month interbank rate in the United Kingdom. This is the interest rate charged by banks on loans to other banks for repayment within three months.

name: United Kingdom - Import Prices
description: This monthly index tracks changes in import prices. The index rises if imports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: United Kingdom - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: United Kingdom - Industrial Production
description: The year-over-year percent change in the monthly industrial production of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Industrial Production MoM
description: The monthly percent change in the industrial production of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Interest Rate
description: The daily average of the central bank policy rate in the United Kingdom. This is the interest rate the central bank charges on loans to commercial banks.

name: United Kingdom - Job Vacancies
description: The total number of job vacancies in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Labour Costs
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in the share of labor in total production costs in the United Kingdom. The index rises when the share of labor rises and falls when the share of labor falls.

name: United Kingdom - Loans to Private Sector
description: The total value of bank loans to the private sector of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Long Term Unemployment Rate
description: The fraction of eligible workers who have been unemployed and looking for work for an extended period of time. Long-term is twelve months in Europe and twenty-seven weeks in the United States.

name: United Kingdom - Money Supply M0
description: The value of physical currency circulating in the economy and the liquid assets held by the central bank.

name: United Kingdom - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: United Kingdom - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: United Kingdom - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: United Kingdom - Average Weekly Wages in Manufacturing
description: The monthly average of the weekly wage in the manufacturing sector of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - UK Finance Mortgage Approvals
description: This index tracks the number of mortgage applications each month in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Mortgage Approvals
description: The number of mortgage approvals by month in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Minimum Hourly Wage
description: The minimum wage in the United Kingdom.
source: Department for Work and Pensions, UK

name: United Kingdom - UK FTSE 100 Stock Market Index
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Manufacturing Production
description: The monthly per cent change in manufacturing output.

name: United Kingdom - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in the United Kingdom. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: United Kingdom - New Orders
description: The market value of new orders of manufactured goods in the United Kingdom by month.

name: United Kingdom - Crude Oil Production
description: the United Kingdom crude oil production in barrels.

name: United Kingdom - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in the United Kingdom, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: United Kingdom - Population
description: The number of residents of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in the United Kingdom. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: United Kingdom - Producer Prices Change
description: The monthly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Productivity
description: This index tracks change in output per worker in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Household Saving Ratio
description: The percentage of income saved by the average household in the United Kingdom, calculated by dividing household savings by disposable income.

name: United Kingdom - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Services PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the overall health of the services sector in the United Kingdom. Private sector reports on key quantitative indicators are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the services sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration in the indicators from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: United Kingdom - Social Security Rate
description: The tax on labor income in the United Kingdom used to fund social assistance programs.

name: United Kingdom - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in the United Kingdom used to fund social assistance programs.

name: United Kingdom - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in the United Kingdom used to fund social assistance programs.

name: United Kingdom - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Terms of Trade
description: The monthly ratio of export prices to import prices in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Tourist Arrivals
description: The number of tourists visiting the United Kingdom from foreign countries.

name: United Kingdom - Unemployed Persons
description: The total members of the labor force of the United Kingdom who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: United Kingdom - Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of the labor force of the United Kingdom who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: United Kingdom - Youth Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of unemployed persons ages 15-29 in the United Kingdom who are actively seeking work.

name: United Kingdom - Average Weekly Wages
description: The monthly average of the weekly nominal wage in the United Kingdom.

name: United Kingdom - Average Weekly Earnings Growth
United Kingdom - Zew Economic Sentiment Index
description: This monthly index tracks economists' expectations for the European economy.

name: Greece - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Greece. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Indonesia - Gross External Debt
description: The total amount of public and private debt in Indonesia owned by foreign creditors.

name: Indonesia - Employed Persons
description: The total number of employed (including self-employed) persons in Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - Export Prices
description: This monthly index tracks changes in the average price of exports in Indonesia. The value of this index is the current price level expressed as a percentage of the price level from 2000. The index rises if exports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: Indonesia - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Indonesia and purchased by foreign entities.

name: Indonesia - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Indonesia. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.

name: Indonesia - Foreign Exchange Reserves
description: The market value of the foreign currency reserves held by Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Indonesia as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.
source: Ministry of Finance of Republic of Indonesia

name: Indonesia - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of Indonesia. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.
source: Ministry of Finance of Republic of Indonesia

name: Indonesia - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - GDP Deflator
description: The relative difference between the real and nominal GDPs of Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - Government Debt to GDP

name: Indonesia - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Indonesia, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: Indonesia - GDP Growth Rate
description: The growth rate of the GDP of Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - Gross National Product
description: The total value of all the final goods and services produced by residents of Indonesia at home and abroad.

name: Indonesia - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: Indonesia - GDP per capita PPP

name: Indonesia - Import Prices

name: Indonesia - Money Supply M0
description: The value of physical currency circulating in the economy and the liquid assets held by the central bank.

description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: Indonesia - Money Supply M2

name: Indonesia - Average Monthly Wages in Manufacturing
description: The average monthly wage in the manufacturing sector of Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - Stock Market (JCI)
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in Indonesia.

name: Indonesia - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Indonesia. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: India - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: India - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Israel - Manufacturing Pmi
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Israel. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. name: Italy - Loans to Private Sector
description: The total value of bank loans to the private sector of Italy.

name: Italy - Long Term Unemployment Rate
description: The fraction of eligible workers who have been unemployed and looking for work for an extended period of time. Long-term is twelve months in Europe and twenty-seven weeks in the United States.

name: Italy - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: Italy - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: Italy - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: Italy - Hourly Wages Index in Industry
description: This monthly index tracks the average hourly wage in the industrial sector of Italy.

name: Italy - Stock Market (FTSE MIB)
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in Italy.

name: Italy - Manufacturing Production
description: The monthly per cent change in manufacturing output.

name: Italy - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Italy. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Italy - Industrial New Orders
description: The market value of new orders of manufactured goods in Italy by month.

name: Italy - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Italy, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: Italy - Population
description: The number of residents of Italy.

name: Italy - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Italy. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: Italy - Producer Prices Change
description: The monthly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of Italy.

name: Italy - Productivity
description: This index tracks change in output per worker in Italy.

name: Italy - Gross Household Saving Rate
description: The percentage of disposal income saved in Italy

name: Italy - Remittances
description: The quarterly net value of remittances into Italy. Remittances are monies sent into Italy by workers in foreign countries.

name: Italy - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in Italy.

name: Italy - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in Italy.

name: Italy - Services PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the overall health of the services sector in Italy. Private sector reports on key quantitative indicators are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the services sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration in the indicators from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Italy - Social Security Rate
description: The tax on labor income in Italy used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Italy - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in Italy used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Italy - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in Italy used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Italy - Sales Tax Rate | VAT
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Italy.

description: The monthly ratio of export prices to import prices in Italy.

name: Italy - Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of the labor force of Italy who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: Italy - Youth Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of unemployed persons ages 15-29 in Italy who are actively seeking work.
