name: Jamaica - Balance of Trade
description: The quarterly net financial position of Jamaica in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Jamaica - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Jamaica - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Jamaica expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Jamaica - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Jamaica, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Jamaica - Consumer Price Index Cpi
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Japan - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Japan in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Japan - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Kenya - Bank Lending Rate
description: The monthly average of the bank lending rate. The bank lending rate is the interest rate charged by banks on loans to the private sector.

name: Kenya - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Kenya in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Kenya - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Kenya - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Kenya expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Kenya - Capital Flows
description: The monthly net capital flow into Kenya for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.

name: Kenya - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Kenya, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Kenya - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

description: The growth rate of the prices in Kenya.

name: Kuwait - Bank Lending Rate
description: The quarterly average of the bank lending rate. The bank lending rate is the interest rate charged by banks on loans to the private sector.

name: Kuwait - Balance of Trade
description: The quarterly net financial position of Kuwait in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Kuwait - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Kuwait - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Kuwait expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Kuwait - Capital Flows
description: The annual net capital flow into Kuwait for the purposes of investment, trade, or production. A positive number indicates a net capital inflow; a negative number indicates a net capital outflow.

name: Kuwait - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Kuwait, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Kuwait - Consumer Price Index Cpi
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Kuwait - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Consumer Spending
description: Total annual personal expenditure on goods and services in Kuwait, excluding interest payments, land purchases, transfers abroad, business expenditures, and purchases of second-hand goods.

name: Kuwait - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Kuwait and purchased by foreign entities.

name: Kuwait - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Kuwait. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.

name: Kuwait - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Kuwait as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.

name: Kuwait - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of Kuwait. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.

name: Kuwait - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in Kuwait as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Kuwait - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Kuwait, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: Kuwait - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: Kuwait - GDP per capita PPP
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: Kuwait - Government Spending
description: The yearly expenditure of the federal government of Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: Kuwait - Interest Rate
description: The daily average of the central bank policy rate in Kuwait. This is the interest rate the central bank charges on loans to commercial banks.

name: Kuwait - Loan Growth
description: The growth rate of the total value of outstanding loans to the private sector in Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: Kuwait - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: Kuwait - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: Kuwait - Stock Exchange Index
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Crude Oil Production
description: Kuwait crude oil production in barrels.

name: Kuwait - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Kuwait, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: Kuwait - Population
description: The number of residents of Kuwait.

name: Kuwait - Wholesale Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Kuwait. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

description: The percentage of the labor force of Kuwait who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Lebanon. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Sri Lanka - Population
description: The number of residents of Sri Lanka.

name: Sri Lanka - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Sri Lanka. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: Sri Lanka - Producer Prices Change
description: The monthly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of Sri Lanka.
source: Department of Census and Statistics - Sri Lanka

name: Sri Lanka - Household Saving Ratio
description: The percentage of income saved by the average household in Sri Lanka. It is calculated by dividing household savings by disposable income.

name: Sri Lanka - Private Sector Credit
description: The monthly change in outstanding private debt in Sri Lanka.

name: Sri Lanka - Services PMI
description: This index tracks the performance of key quantitative indicators in the services sector of Sri Lanka. Index values over 50 suggest economic expansion within the service sector; index values under 50 indicate economic contraction within the service sector.

name: Sri Lanka - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in Sri Lanka used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Sri Lanka - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in Sri Lanka used to fund social assistance programs.

name: Sri Lanka - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Sri Lanka.

name: Sri Lanka - Terms of Trade
description: The monthly ratio of export prices to import prices in Sri Lanka.

name: Sri Lanka - Tourist Arrivals
description: The number of tourists visiting Sri Lanka from foreign countries.

name: Sri Lanka - Unemployed Persons
description: The total members of the labor force of Sri Lanka who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: Sri Lanka - Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of the labor force of Sri Lanka who are unemployed and actively seeking work.
source: Department of Census and Statistics - Sri Lanka

name: Sri Lanka - Wages
description: This index tracks the average yearly wage in Sri Lanka.

name: Lesotho - Balance of Trade
description: The quarterly net financial position of Lesotho in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Lesotho - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Lesotho - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Lesotho expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Lesotho - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Lesotho, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Lesotho - Consumer Price Index Cpi
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Lesotho - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Lesotho.

name: Lesotho - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in Lesotho.

name: Lesotho - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Lesotho and purchased by foreign entities.

name: Lesotho - Food Inflation
description: The growth rate of food prices in Lesotho.

name: Lesotho - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Lesotho.

name: Lesotho - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Lesotho.

name: Lesotho - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Lesotho as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.

name: Lesotho - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in Lesotho as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Lesotho - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: Lesotho - GDP per capita PPP
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: Lesotho - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Lithuania and purchased by foreign entities.

name: Lithuania - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Lithuania. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.

name: Lithuania - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the Lithuania.

name: Lithuania - GDP Deflator
description: The relative difference between the real and nominal GDPs of Lithuania.

name: Latvia - Money Supply M0
description: The value of physical currency circulating in the economy and the liquid assets held by the central bank.

name: Latvia - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: Latvia - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: Latvia - Gross Minimum Monthly Wage
description: The minimum wage in Latvia.

name: Latvia - Stock Market (OMX Riga)
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in Latvia.

name: Latvia - Manufacturing Production
description: The monthly per cent change in manufacturing output.

name: Latvia - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Latvia, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: Latvia - Population
description: The number of residents of Latvia.

name: Latvia - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Latvia. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: Latvia - Producer Prices Change
description: The monthly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of Latvia.

name: Latvia - Gross Household Saving Rate

name: Latvia - Retail Sales MoM

name: Macau - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of Macau in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - Current Account to Gdp
description: The current account balance of Macau expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Macau - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Macau.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - Consumer Spending
description: Total quarterly personal expenditure on goods and services in Macau, excluding interest payments, land purchases, transfers abroad, business expenditures, and purchases of second-hand goods.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in Macau.

name: Macau - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Macau and purchased by foreign entities.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - Foreign Direct Investment - Net Flows
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Macau. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Macau.

name: Macau - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Macau.
source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: Macau - GDP per capita PPP
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: Macau - Imports

source: Statistics and Census Service, Government of Macao SAR

name: Macau - Interest Rate

description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Mexico. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. name: Macedonia - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Malaysia. description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Namibia - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Poland - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Qatar - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Russia - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Russia. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: Saudi Arabia - Balance of Trade
description: The quarterly net financial position of Saudi Arabia in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: Saudi Arabia - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Saudi Arabia - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of Saudi Arabia, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: Saudi Arabia - Consumer Confidence
description: This quarterly index tracks consumers' opinions about their current economic well-being and outlook for the economy. It provides insight into consumers' short-term spending, saving, and borrowing plans.

name: Saudi Arabia - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Slovenia - Business Confidence

name: Slovenia - Balance of Trade

name: Slovenia - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

description: The current account balance of Slovenia expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Slovenia - Consumer Credit

name: Slovenia - Construction Output

name: Slovenia - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.
source: Statistical Office of the Republic of Slovenia

name: Sweden - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Sweden. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.
source: Central Bureau of Statistics, Syrian Arab Republic

name: Syria - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Syria.
source: Central Bureau of Statistics, Syrian Arab Republic

name: Syria - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Syria, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: Thailand - Manufacturing Pmi
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Thailand. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in Turkey. name: United States - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: United States - Consumer Inflation Expectations
source: Federal Reserve Bank of New York

name: United States - Industrial Production
description: The year-over-year percent change in the monthly industrial production of the United States.

name: United States - Industrial Production MoM
description: The monthly percent change in the industrial production of the United States.

name: United States - Fed Funds Rate
description: The monthly average of the central bank policy rate in the United States, commonly referred to as the Fed Funds Target Rate. This is the interest rate the central bank targets for loans to commercial banks. In the US, the rate is set by the FOMC.

name: United States - ISM New York Index
United States - Initial Jobless Claims
description: The weekly number of first-time jobless claims in the United States; an indicator of new  unemployment.

name: United States - Job Vacancies
description: The total number of job vacancies in the United States.

name: United States - Nonfarm Unit Labour Cost
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in the share of labor in total production costs in the United States. The index rises when the share of labor rises and falls when the share of labor falls.

name: United States - Labor Force Participation Rate
description: The percentage of working-age persons in the United States who are employed or seeking employment

name: United States - Loans to Private Sector
description: The total value of bank loans to the private sector of the United States.

name: United States - Long Term Unemployment Rate
description: The fraction of eligible workers who have been unemployed and looking for work for an extended period of time. Long-term is twelve months in Europe and twenty-seven weeks in the United States.

name: United States - Money Supply M0
description: The value of physical currency circulating in the economy and the liquid assets held by the central bank.

name: United States - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: United States - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: United States - Average Hourly Wages in Manufacturing
description: The monthly average of the hourly wage in the manufacturing sector of the United States.

name: United States - MBA Mortgage Applications
description: This index tracks the number of mortgage applications each week in the United States.

name: United States - Dow Jones Industrial Average
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in the United States.

name: United States - MBA 30-Yr Mortgage Rate
description: The weekly average of the interest rate on thirty-year mortgages

name: United States - Manufacturing Production
description: The monthly per cent change in manufacturing output.

name: United States - Manufacturing Payrolls
description: Net employment change in the manufacturing sector of the United States, i.e. the total number of people hired or fired each month.

name: United States - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in the United States. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: United States - Nahb Housing Market Index
description: This index tracks measures sales conditions for new homes bases on builders sentiment.  The National Association of Home Builders surveys 140,000 members, polling them on their impression of conditions now, conditions in 6 months, and their sense of buyer demand levels.  The index can range from 0 to 100; a reading over 50 indicates that more builders view sales conditions as favorable compared with those who view them as unfavorable.

name: United States - Natural Gas Stocks ChangeÂ
United States - Nfib Business Optimism Index
description: This index measures economic trends in the small business sector. It tracks quantitative indicators like job vacancies and inventories, and qualitative variables like plans to increase employment. Altogether, the index combines a snapshot of current conditions with predictions for the future. It is composed of surveys of small businesses drawn from NFIB's membership.

name: United States - Non Farm Payrolls
description: The monthly net employment change in the non-agricultural economic sectors of the United States.

name: United States - New Home Sales
description: The number of new homes sold in the United States, including houses at all stages of construction.

name: United States - Net Long-Term TIC Flows
description: The monthly net flow of Treasury and agency securities, as well as corporate bonds and equities, into the United States.

name: United States - Non Manufacturing PMI
description: The percentage of survey respondents in the non-manufacturing sector who report improving business conditions.  PMI above (below) 50% suggests an expansion (contraction) in the non-manufacturing sector of the economy.

name: United States - New Orders
description: The market value of new orders of manufactured goods in the United States by month.

name: United States - Crude Oil Production
description: the United States crude oil production in barrels.

name: United States - IBD/TIPP Economic Optimism Index
description: This index measures consumer opinions on the outlook of the national economy in the United States. It is based on a nationwide survey of working-age adults on their personal financial outlook, economic outlook, and confidence in federal economic policies. An index value of 50 indicates no change from the previous survey.
source: Technometrica Market Intelligence/The Investor's Business Daily

name: United States - Personal Consumption Expenditure Price Index
United States - Philadelphia Fed Manufacturing Index
description: This index tracks manufacturing growth in the third Federal Reserve District.  The index is constructed from a survey of participants who voluntarily answer questions regarding the direction of change in their overall business activities. An index value above (below) 0 is associated with expansion (contraction) in the manufacturing sector.

name: United States - Pending Home Sales
description: This index tracks pending home sales in the United States.  A sale is pending if a contract has been signed but the transaction has not closed; i.e. payment has not been made by the buyer.

name: United States - Personal Income
description: monthly per cent changes in total income earned by individuals before taxes and deductions in the United States.

name: United States - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in the United States, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: United States - Population
description: The number of residents of the United States.

name: United States - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in the United States. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: United States - Producer Prices Change
description: The monthly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of the United States.

name: United States - Nonfarm Labour Productivity
description: This index tracks change in output per worker in the United States.

name: United States - Personal Savings Rate
description: The percentage of disposal income saved in the United States

name: United States - Personal Spending
description: The monthly percent change in personal consumption spending in the United States.

name: United States - Redbook Index
description: This index tracks total weekly retail sales in the United States. It is published by Redbook Research Inc.

name: United States - Retail Sales Ex Autos MoM
United States - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in the United States.

name: United States - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in the United States.

name: United States - Services PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the overall health of the services sector in the United States. Private sector reports on key quantitative indicators are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the services sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration in the indicators from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: United States - Social Security Rate
description: The tax on labor income in the United States used to fund social assistance programs.

name: United States - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in the United States used to fund social assistance programs.

name: United States - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in the United States used to fund social assistance programs.

name: United States - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in the United States.

name: United States - Terms of Trade
description: The quarterly ratio of export prices to import prices in the United States.

name: United States - Tourist Arrivals
description: The number of tourists visiting the United States from foreign countries.
source: Office of Travel and Tourism Industries

name: United States - Total Vehicle Sales
description: The number of new vehicles sold in the United States.

name: United States - Unemployed Persons
description: The total members of the labor force of the United States who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: United States - Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of the labor force of the United States who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: United States - Youth Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of unemployed persons ages 15-29 in the United States who are actively seeking work.

name: United States - Average Hourly Wages
description: The monthly average of the hourly wage in the United States.

name: United States - Wholesale Inventories
description: The monthly inventory levels of wholesalers in the United States.

name: Uzbekistan - Balance of Trade
description: The quarterly net financial position of Uzbekistan in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.
source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

name: Uzbekistan - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: Uzbekistan - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of Uzbekistan expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: Uzbekistan - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Uzbekistan.
source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

name: Uzbekistan - Consumer Spending
description: Total annual personal expenditure on goods and services in Uzbekistan, excluding interest payments, land purchases, transfers abroad, business expenditures, and purchases of second-hand goods.

name: Uzbekistan - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in Uzbekistan.

name: Uzbekistan - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Uzbekistan and purchased by foreign entities.
source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

name: Uzbekistan - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Uzbekistan.

name: Uzbekistan - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Uzbekistan.

name: Uzbekistan - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Uzbekistan as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.
source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

name: Uzbekistan - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in Uzbekistan as a percentage of its GDP.
source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

name: Uzbekistan - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Uzbekistan, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.
source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

name: Uzbekistan - Industrial Production

description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Uzbekistan, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

source: The State Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan on Statistics

description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Uzbekistan.

description: This index tracks prices of consumer goods excluding food, energy and other items with high price volatility.

name: Venezuela - Core Inflation Rate
description: The rate of change of the core Consumer Price Index of Venezuela.

name: Venezuela - Consumer Confidence
description: This quarterly index tracks consumers' opinions about their current economic well-being and outlook for the economy. It provides insight into consumers' short-term spending, saving, and borrowing plans.

name: Venezuela - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: Venezuela - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in Venezuela.

name: Venezuela - Inflation Rate MoM

description: The annual change in inventory levels in Kosovo.

name: Kosovo - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by Kosovo and purchased by foreign entities.

name: Kosovo - Foreign Direct Investment - Net Inflows
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in Kosovo. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.
source: Central Bank of the Republic of Kosovo

name: Kosovo - GDP
description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of Kosovo.

name: Kosovo - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in Kosovo.

name: Kosovo - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of Kosovo as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.
source: Central Bank of the Republic of Kosovo

name: Kosovo - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of Kosovo. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.

name: Kosovo - GDP Current Prices
description: An unadjusted measure of GDP in Kosovo.

name: Kosovo - Government Debt To GDP
description: Government debt in Kosovo as a percentage of its GDP.
source: Ministry of Finance, Republic of Kosovo

name: Kosovo - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in Kosovo, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: Kosovo - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: Kosovo - GDP per Capita Ppp
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: Kosovo - General Government Spending
description: The yearly expenditure of the federal government of Kosovo.

name: Kosovo - Import Prices
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in import prices. The index rises if imports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: Kosovo - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: Kosovo - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in Kosovo, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: Kosovo - Population
description: The number of residents of Kosovo.

name: Kosovo - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in Kosovo. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: Kosovo - Producer Prices Change
description: The quarterly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of Kosovo.

name: Kosovo - Social Security Rate For Companies
description: The tax rate on corporate profits in Kosovo used to fund social assistance programs.
source: Ministry Of Labour and Social Welfare

name: Kosovo - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in Kosovo used to fund social assistance programs.
source: Ministry Of Labour and Social Welfare

name: Kosovo - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in Kosovo.
source: Ministry of Finance, Republic of Kosovo

name: Kosovo - Unemployed Persons
description: The total members of the labor force of Kosovo who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: Kosovo - Unemployment Rate
description: The percentage of the labor force of Kosovo who are unemployed and actively seeking work.

name: Kosovo - Average Monthly Wages
description: The average monthly wage in Kosovo.

name: Yemen - Balance of Trade

name: South Africa - Business Confidence
description: This quarterly index tracks the outlook of representative firms on the future business climate of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Prime Overdraft Rate
description: The monthly average of the prime overdraft rate in South Africa. This is the interest rate charged by banks on overdraft loans to their most credit worthy customers.

name: South Africa - Balance of Trade
description: The monthly net financial position of South Africa in the global goods and services market, measured as the difference in value between its imports and exports. A negative trade balance indicates imports exceed exports; a positive trade balance indicates exports exceed imports.

name: South Africa - Bankruptcies
description: The monthly number of corporate bankruptcies in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Current Account
description: The the sum of the balance of trade (goods and services exports less imports), net income from abroad and net current transfers. A positive value indicates that a country is a net lender to the rest of the world; a negative value indicates that a country is a net borrower.

name: South Africa - Current Account to GDP
description: The current account balance of South Africa expressed as a percentage of its GDP.

name: South Africa - New Car Sales
description: The number of new cars sold in South Africa each month.

name: South Africa - Competitiveness Index
description: A measurement of the level of productivity of South Africa, based on a set of institutions, policies and other factors.

name: South Africa - SACCI Business Confidence Index
description: This weighted index of macroeconomic indicators tracks the health of Japan's regional economies. It consists of eleven leading indicators, eleven coincident indicators, and six lagged indicators. Positive values indicate economic expansion; negative values indicate economic contraction.
source: South African Chamber of Commerce and Industry (SACCI)

name: South Africa - Core Inflation RateÂ
description: The rate of change of the core Consumer Price Index of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Consumer Confidence
description: This quarterly index tracks consumers' opinions about their current economic well-being and outlook for the economy. It provides insight into consumers' short-term spending, saving, and borrowing plans.

name: South Africa - Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) is a measure of inflation related to the cost of living. It tracks the prices of essential goods and services like food and healthcare, and weighs those price changes according to their relative importance. The overall change in prices is the inflation rate, which can be positive or negative. The standard CPI fails to account for price drops resulting from improved production technologies, so the chained CPI was crafted to allow for a continuously changing basket of goods.

name: South Africa - Inflation Rate
description: The growth rate of the prices in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Inflation Rate Mom
description: The monthly percent change consumer prices of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Consumer Spending
description: Total quarterly personal expenditure on goods and services in South Africa, excluding interest payments, land purchases, transfers abroad, business expenditures, and purchases of second-hand goods.
units: ZAR Million Constant Prices 2010, SA & Annualized

name: South Africa - Corporate Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on corporate profits in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Capacity Utilization
description: The quarterly national output of South Africa as a percentage of its potential national output.

name: South Africa - Changes in Inventories

name: South Africa - Disposable Personal Income

name: South Africa - Gross External Debt
description: The total amount of public and private debt in South Africa owned by foreign creditors.

name: South Africa - Employed Persons
description: The total number of employed (including self-employed) persons in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Export Prices
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in the average price of exports in South Africa. The value of this index is the current price level expressed as a percentage of the price level from 2000. The index rises if exports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: South Africa - Exports
description: The total value of the goods and services produced by South Africa and purchased by foreign entities.

name: South Africa - Foreign Direct Investment
description: The value of all investments made by foreign entities directly into companies in South Africa. It does not include foreign purchases of equities on domestic stock exchanges.

name: South Africa - Foreign Exchange Reserves
description: The market value of the foreign currency reserves held by South Africa.

description: The growth rate of food prices in South Africa.

description: The unadjusted gross domestic product of South Africa.

name: South Africa - GDP Annual Growth Rate
description: The annual growth rate of GDP in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Government Budget
description: The federal government budget of South Africa as a percentage of its GDP. Negative values denote budget deficits; positive values denote budget surpluses.

name: South Africa - Government Budget Value
description: The balance of the federal budget of South Africa. It consists of tax revenues and expenses on government services. Negative budget values denote budget deficits; positive budget values denote budget surpluses.

name: South Africa - GDP Constant Prices
description: An inflation-adjusted measure of GDP in the South Africa.

name: South Africa - Government Debt to GDP
description: Government debt in South Africa as a percentage of its GDP.

name: South Africa - Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: The net value of fixed capital flowing into businesses in South Africa, where fixed capital is the value of new fixed capital purchased by businesses less old fixed capital sold or disposed of, ignoring depreciation costs of existing fixed assets.

name: South Africa - GDP Growth Rate
description: The growth rate of the GDP of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Gross National Income
description: The total income earned by residents of South Africa at home and abroad.

name: South Africa - Gold Reserves
description: The market value of the gold reserves held by the central bank of South Africa.

name: South Africa - GDP per capita
description: Gross Domestic Product per capita

name: South Africa - GDP per capita PPP
description: GDP per capita in International dollars

name: South Africa - Government Spending
description: The yearly expenditure of the federal government of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Government Bond 10Y
description: The average of the yield on ten-year government bonds in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Three Month Interbank Rate
description: The daily average of the interbank rate in South Africa. The interbank rate is the interest rate charged by banks on loans to other banks.

name: South Africa - Import Prices
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in import prices. The index rises if imports become more expensive and falls if they get cheaper.

name: South Africa - Imports
description: The total value of a country's imports of physical goods and payments to foreigners for services like shipping and tourism.

name: South Africa - Manufacturing Production
description: The year-over-year percent change in the monthly industrial production of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Industrial Production MoM
description: The monthly percent change in the industrial production of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Interest Rate
description: The daily average of the central bank policy rate in South Africa. This is the interest rate the central bank charges on loans to commercial banks.

name: South Africa - Labour Costs
description: This quarterly index tracks changes in the share of labor in total production costs in South Africa. The index rises when the share of labor rises and falls when the share of labor falls.

name: South Africa - Labor Force Participation Rate
description: The percentage of working-age persons in South Africa who are employed or seeking employment

name: South Africa - Loans to Private Sector
description: The total value of bank loans to the private sector of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Money Supply M0
description: The value of physical currency circulating in the economy and the liquid assets held by the central bank.

name: South Africa - Money Supply M1
description: M0 + the money in transactional bank accounts like checking accounts, demand deposits, and travelers' checks.

name: South Africa - Money Supply M2
description: M1 + savings deposits, small-denomination savings deposits, and retail money market mutual funds.

name: South Africa - Money Supply M3
description: M2 + large-time deposits, institutional money market funds, short-term repurchase agreements and other larger liquid assets.

name: South Africa - Total Quarterly Wages in Manufacturing
description: Total quarterly wages earned by the manufacturing sector of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Stock Market
description: A stock market index which tracks the performance of a selection of larger and more liquid companies based in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Manufacturing PMI
description: This monthly index tracks the health of the manufacturing sector in South Africa. Private sector companies report improvement or deterioration in key quantitative indicators like new orders, production, inventories, and employment levels. Responses are amalgamated into an index whose value indicates expansion or contraction of the manufacturing sector. A PMI of 50% means equal numbers of respondents reported improvement and deterioration and there is no change from the previous month; PMIs above and below 50% indicate expansion and contraction of the sector respectively.

name: South Africa - Personal Income Tax Rate
description: The top marginal tax rate on personal income in South Africa, including income earned from labor, pensions, interest, and dividends.

name: South Africa - Population
description: The number of residents of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Producer Prices
description: This index tracks the average prices domestic producers receive for their output in South Africa. These are the prices of final goods as they leave the factory gate rather than the prices set by wholesalers and resellers.

name: South Africa - Producer Prices Change
description: The monthly percent change in the Producer Prices Index of South Africa.

name: South Africa - Household Saving Ratio
description: The total amount of income saved by households in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Private Sector Credit
description: The monthly change in outstanding private debt in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Retail Sales MoM
description: The monthly percent change in total retail sales in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Retail Sales YoY
description: The per cent change in total monthly retail sales relative to one year earlier in South Africa.

name: South Africa - Social Security Rate
description: The tax on labor income in South Africa used to fund social assistance programs.

description: The tax rate on corporate profits in South Africa used to fund social assistance programs.

name: South Africa - Social Security Rate For Employees
description: The tax on wages in South Africa used to fund social assistance programs.

name: South Africa - Sales Tax Rate
description: The federal sales tax rate on goods and services in South Africa.

description: The number of tourists visiting South Africa from foreign countries.

description: The number of new vehicles sold in South Africa.
